%N A396222 a(n) = T(n, n + 2), where T(n, m) is the forward-difference table of the Catalan numbers.
%C A396222 Let T(0, m) = A000108(m) and T(n, m) = T(n - 1, m + 1) - T(n - 1, m). Then a(n) = T(n, n + 2). This is a shifted diagonal of the Catalan forward-difference table.
%F A396222 a(n) = T(n, n + 2).
%F A396222 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} (-1)^(n - k)*binomial(n, k)*A000108(n + 2 + k).
%e A396222 The array T(n, m) begins:
%e A396222   n = 0:  1  1   2   5   14   42  132  ...
%e A396222   n = 1:  0  1   3   9   28   90  297  ...
%e A396222   n = 2:  1  2   6  19   62  207  ...
%e A396222   n = 3:  1  4  13  43  145  497  ...
%e A396222 a(2) = T(2, 4) = 62.
%e A396222 a(3) = T(3, 5) = 497.
